Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.
Put #aluminum foil{} on baking sheet for easy cleanup. Roast on top rack until
browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Carefully toss roasted broccoli with half the @sesame dressing{1.5%ounce}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.
Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and 3⁄4 cup water. Bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. Keep
covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon},
@ponzu sauce{6%milliliters}, @plum jam{1}, garlic, @cornstarch{1%tablespoon},
remaining sesame dressing, and 1⁄4 cup water; stir until no lumps remain.

Pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; prick all over with a #fork{}.
Season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> Press pork down with a spatula to ensure even browning.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Heat pan used for pork over medium heat. Stir in 1⁄4 cup water; scrape up any
browned bits from bottom of pan, ~{30%seconds}. Add hoisin mixture and cook,
stirring, until thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with
salt and pepper.

> If sauce seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Transfer pork to pan with sauce; turn to coat.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide broccoli, rice, and pork between plates. Drizzle pork with any remaining
sauce and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve.